message.text:
Political representation is more than a seat at the table. It’s rewriting the rules of the table itself.

When women lead, they don’t just sign policies; they challenge broken systems, amplify silenced voices, and demand futures that include everyone.

Your political views are not just opinions they are reflections of what you believe is right, just, and possible.

Do you stand for progress, or cling to patriarchy?
Do you choose justice, or the walls built by fear?

The world we wake up to tomorrow depends on the 
choices we make today.

Caption by: Julienne Alyssa Manuel
Pubmat by: Inca Marie Mangubat

Do you stand for progress, or cling to patriarchy?
Do you choose justice, or the walls built by fear?

The world we wake up to tomorrow depends on the 
choices we make today.

message.text:
Political representation is more than a seat at the table. It’s rewriting the rules of the table itself.

When women lead, they don’t just sign policies; they challenge broken systems, amplify silenced voices, and demand futures that include everyone.

Your political views are not just opinions they are reflections of what you believe is right, just, and possible.

Do you stand for progress, or cling to patriarchy?
Do you choose justice, or the walls built by fear?

The world we wake up to tomorrow depends on the 
choices we make today.

Caption by: Julienne Alyssa Manuel
Pubmat by: Inca Marie Mangubat
